@startuml
title Query Loop Recovery Branches - Controlled Side Paths

skinparam backgroundColor #F7F1E6
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 130
skinparam defaultFontName Georgia
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam TitleFontSize 19
skinparam TitleFontColor #161616
skinparam NoteFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowColor #5E5A53
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #F2E9D9
  BorderColor #1D1D1D
  FontColor #161616
  ArrowColor #5E5A53
  StartColor #8C2721
  EndColor #161616
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F5EBDD
  BorderColor #8C2721
  FontColor #7B1E1E
}

[*] --> Trigger

state "Recovery trigger" as Trigger #F5EBDD
state "PTL: collapse drain" as Drain
state "PTL: reactive compact" as Compact
state "MOT: raise cap" as RaiseCap
state "MOT: inject resume" as Resume
state "Interrupt: yield pending" as Yield
state "API/hook: classify\n+ retry policy" as Classify
state "Post-compact messages" as Post #EFE6D8
state "Re-enter Prepare" as Reenter #EFE6D8
state "Surface error" as Surface #F5EBDD
state "Interruption end" as End #F5EBDD

Trigger --> Drain : prompt too long
Drain --> Reenter : resolved
Drain --> Compact : still over budget
Compact --> Post : summary fits
Compact --> Surface : compact fails
Post --> Reenter

Trigger --> RaiseCap : max_output_tokens
RaiseCap --> Resume : cap not cheap
RaiseCap --> Reenter : cap raised
Resume --> Reenter

Trigger --> Yield : user interrupt
Yield --> End

Trigger --> Classify : api / tool / hook failure
Classify --> Reenter : retryable
Classify --> Surface : not retryable

Reenter --> [*]
Surface --> [*]
End --> [*]

note right of Reenter
  Every recoverable branch
  ends the same way: back
  into Prepare or a
  deterministic exit.
  Recovery is a first-class
  path, not a patch.
end note

@enduml
